verbose_text: After adjustment for BMI, family history of hypertension, education, profession, salt intake, HR, blood lipid, and fasting glucose levels, these associations were attenuated and remained significant only for 16:1 n-7 (OR 1.74; 95% CI, 1.05-2.89; P for trend = 0.040) and 22:6 n-3 (OR 0.68; 95% CI, 0.47-0.98; P for trend = 0.048).
